reviews.review_text:
where is this filler from? The 1st filler (drums, good lovin, china/rider, good lovin) is warbly with lots of technical problems, sounds like a beat up AUD of some old 69' show. But the energy is through the roof!! People sound like they are going absolutely BONKERS during Good Lovin!!!! Love it. Makes me wish so bad I could have been there for the craziness that must have been going on. Any idea what show this filler is from?  

The Dark Star filler portion is of much higher quality, SBD source for this part. 

Oh yeah, as for the original show, China>Rider>Estimated>Eyes is pretty sweet (of course!) :-)

Review of the review 5 stars for using bonkers...will do real review soon...sorry for miss use of the review portion, but bonkers is the right word and someone had to say it. I will give a real rating though, so as not to mess up the average.

pretty good There are some great moments but a lot of vocal lapses and a few musical ones as well. Certainly worth hearing and delightful at points but not in the class of others that are just 'on' the whole way through.

This is why CM is the best The tracks on this are done wrong.  The song should start within seconds of starting.  Instead there is dead silence for a minute in some cases.  Just seems like common sense that no one wants to hear 60 seconds of tuning and crowd noise before hearing the actual song.  Charlie Miller transfers are the best.
